    "client_msg_id": "f25183c5-7141-43cc-9b77-4df2f16ca034",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "It doesn’t exist in public at all at this point, I’m still hoping to hustle up something at work in the area.\n\nAll my experimentation has been in the area of web applications – the browser interface is well-defined and sandboxed, so you can really tell what can and cannot cause changes in an application (e.g., which elements have event listeners). Browser debugging interfaces also offer a well-documented way to inspect relatively high-level behavior.\n\nI’ve been able to generate random runs in real-world applications, but I haven’t convinced myself that I can actually thoroughly explore an application automatically. And then generating _insight_ from those runs is also something I haven’t managed to do. So it’s pretty early-stage.",
